        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued August 24 at 7:16PM CDT until August 24 at 7:45PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 716 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 6 miles south of
Lake Marvin, or 15 miles southeast of Canadian, moving south at 25
mph.

HAZARD...Two inch hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to roofs, siding, and trees is possible.
People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles.

This severe thunderstorm will remain over mainly rural areas of
southeastern Hemphill County.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Torrential rainfall is occurring with this storm, and may lead to
flash flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
